xxl.core.indexStructures

Class FixedQuery<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.indexStructures.FixedQuery<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The data type of the set
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Set<E>, SortedSet<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BPlusIndexedSetView

    public abstract class FixedQuery<E>
extends Object
implements SortedSet<E>
    A subclass of AbstractView is a fixed non-editable portion of data of a IndexedSet. By sub setting an IndexedSet you setup a lower and a upper bound. All entries which are greater or equal to the lower bound and less (depending of the subset kind it's strictly less or also equal to) the upper bound will be visible inside the view. Depending on the implementation of AbstractView some methods of the SortedSet interface will not be available. Please consider documentation of the individual sub classes.

    Please note: Although you can not edit the content of a view, it's content will be refreshed automatically if the source set changes. That means if a view v contains an item e and you remove e from the parent set, e will not be visible in v anymore.

    • Constructor Detail

      • FixedQuery

        public FixedQuery(IndexedSet dataSource,
                  Comparable minBound,
                  Comparable maxBound,
                  boolean excludeToElement)
        Constructs a new view for the set dataSource with the given boundaries. If it is necessary to exclude the last element, set excludeToElement to true. Otherwise the view will contains elements which are less or equal to the last element.
        Parameters:
        dataSource - The parent set
        minBound - The lower bound
        maxBound - The upper bound
        excludeToElement - Flag to indicate how to handle elements relative to the upper bound
